http://superuser.com/questions/272925/ubuntu-behaves-as-if-i-have-two-clipboards/272934#272934
https://specifications.freedesktop.org/clipboards-spec/clipboards-latest.txt

X actually has three clipboards. Highlighting text moves it into one clipboard (PRIMARY),
performing a copy operation copies it to a second (CLIPBOARD), and the third clipboard [SECONDARY]
is almost never used.
